Title : Mount Saugstad
Text : '''Mount Saugstad''' is a [[mountain]] in the northernmost [[Pacific Ranges]] of the [[Coast Mountains]] in the [[British Columbia Coast|Central Coast region]] of [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]].  It is located just south of the community of [[Hagensborg]] in the [[Bella Coola Valley]] and is immediately southeast of [[Snootli Peak]] and also southeast of Big Snow Mountain.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/17162.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Mount Saugstad"]</ref>  The [[Smitley River]] has its origins on the west side of the summit<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/21699.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Smitley River"]</ref> at the '''Saugstad Glacier''', which is at {{coord|52|15|48|N|126|31|36|W|display=inline|source:BCNames}}<ref>][http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/17162.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Saugstad Glacier"]</ref>

==Name origin==
Mount Saugstad was named for the Reverend [[Christian Saugstad]], the leader of a Norwegian colony in [[Minnesota]] who was encouraged to move the colony to [[Bella Coola, British Columbia|Bella Coola]] by settler B.F. Jacobsen, who had moved to the area prior to 1890.  The Reverend Saugstad was the pastor of the local congregation until his death in 1897.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/17162.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Mount Saugstad"]</ref>  [[Mount Jacobsen]] to the southeast was named for B.F. Jacobsen.\<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/9571.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Mount Jacobsen"]</ref> with adjacent West Jacobsen Peak in the same massif following suit.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/37739.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "West Jacobsen Peak"]</ref>

